measure.name: Disinfection
measure.description: Application, after thorough cleansing, of procedures intended to destroy the infectious or parasitic agents of animal diseases, including zoonoses; this applies to premises, vehicles and different objects which may have been directly or indirectly contaminated.

measure.name: Movement control
measure.description: Measures aimed at avoiding the spread of the disease, infection or infestation within a country/zone/compartment due to the movement of animals or their products.

measure.name: Official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste
measure.description: Disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste under the supervision of the Competent Authority to prevent spread of the disease, infection or infestation.

measure.name: Stamping out
measure.description: The killing of the animals which are affected and those suspected of being affected in the herd or flock and, where appropriate, those in other herds or flocks which have been exposed to infection by direct animal to animal contact, or by indirect contact with the causal pathogenic agent; animals should be killed in accordance with Chapter 7.6. The disposal of carcasses and, where relevant, animal products by rendering, burning or burial, or by any other method described in Chapter 4.12. The cleansing and disinfection of establishments through procedures defined in Chapter 4.13.

measure.name: Surveillance outside the restricted zone
measure.description: Undertaking surveillance activities in parts of the country other than those defined as the containment or protection zone for the disease, infection or infestation being notified.

measure.name: Surveillance within the restricted zone
measure.description: Undertaking surveillance activities within the containment or protection zone for the disease, infection or infestation being notified.

measure.name: Traceability
measure.description: Investigation of any epidemiological link of animals / animal products, in order to determine origin and spread of the disease, infection or infestation.

measure.name: Zoning
measure.description: Delineation (by regulatory means) of part of a country/territory containing an animal subpopulation with a distinct health status or risk with respect to a specific disease, infection or infestation for which required surveillance, control and biosecurity measures have been applied for the purpose of international trade.

measure.description: Undertaking surveillance activities within the containment or protection zone for the disease, infection or infestation being notified.
